(1, 'Everest Base Camp Trek', 3, 'A 12-day guided trek to the legendary Everest Base Camp.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Everest Base Camp Trek Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Everest Base Camp Trek: A Journey to the Top of the World</h1>\r\n    <p>Are you ready for the adventure of a lifetime? Our 12-day guided trek to the legendary Everest Base Camp is more than just a hike; it is a pilgrimage to the heart of the Himalayas. This meticulously planned expedition takes you through stunning landscapes, traditional Sherpa villages, and ancient monasteries, culminating in the breathtaking view of Mount Everest from its base.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Itinerary: A Day-by-Day Adventure</h2>\r\n        <p>Our journey begins in Kathmandu, where you\'ll be welcomed into a world of cultural richness before a scenic flight to Lukla, the gateway to the Everest region. From there, we embark on a steady ascent, acclimatizing properly to the altitude and ensuring a safe and enjoyable experience.</p>\r\n        <p>Highlights of the trek include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 1-2: Arrival & Acclimatization in Kathmandu & Lukla.</strong> We\'ll fly to Lukla and begin our trek to Phakding, surrounded by stunning views.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 3-4: The Heart of Sherpa Country.</strong> Trek to Namche Bazaar, the bustling hub of the Khumbu region. This is a crucial acclimatization stop where we\'ll explore the local markets and monasteries.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 5-6: Towards the Peaks.</strong> Journey to Tengboche, home to the largest monastery in the region, offering panoramic views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 7-9: The High Altitude Push.</strong> We\'ll move through Dingboche and Lobuche, feeling the air thin as we get closer to our goal.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 10-11: EBC and Kala Patthar.</strong> This is the climax of our journey. We will trek to Everest Base Camp, celebrate our achievement, and then ascend Kala Patthar at sunrise for the best views of Everest.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 12: The Descent.</strong> We begin our journey back, filled with unforgettable memories and a sense of accomplishment.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>What Makes Our Trek Unique?</h2>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Experienced Guides:</strong> Our guides are all certified and have extensive knowledge of the Everest region, its culture, and its environment.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Safety First:</strong> We prioritize your safety with a carefully planned itinerary that includes acclimatization days, quality equipment, and a small participant-to-guide ratio.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Cultural Immersion:</strong> We go beyond the trekking trails, giving you a chance to interact with local Sherpa communities and experience their unique way of life.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>All-Inclusive Package:</strong> The price includes all meals, accommodation in comfortable teahouses, permits, and domestic flights, so you can focus on the adventure.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Ready to Join Us?</h2>\r\n        <p>This is a challenging yet highly rewarding trek. While no prior trekking experience is required, a good level of physical fitness is essential. We will provide a detailed packing list and all the information you need to prepare for this epic journey. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-09-01</strong>, so book your spot now and start your adventure to the top of the world!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 12, '1200.00', '12', '2025-09-01 00:00:00', '2025-09-15', '2025-09-27', 'Published', 'Hard', 1, 29, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:34:35'),
(2, 'Intro to Mountaineering', 1, 'Learn the basics of mountaineering including crampon and ice axe use.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Intro to Mountaineering Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Intro to Mountaineering: Your First Step to the High Peaks</h1>\r\n    <p>Have you ever dreamed of climbing a snow-capped mountain but didn\'t know where to start? Our \"Intro to Mountaineering\" course is the perfect gateway to the world of alpine climbing. This comprehensive 2-day program is designed for complete beginners, covering all the essential skills you need to safely and confidently traverse glaciated terrain.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Course Curriculum: Learn the Ropes</h2>\r\n        <p>Our expert instructors will guide you through a hands-on curriculum that blends classroom theory with practical on-mountain application. The goal is to build a strong foundation of skills that will serve you on future climbs.</p>\r\n        <p>Key topics include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Crampon and Ice Axe Techniques:</strong> Master the fundamental skills of walking on snow and ice, self-arrest, and using an ice axe for support.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Rope Team Travel:</strong> Learn how to travel safely on a glacier as part of a rope team, including basic knot tying and rope management.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Glacier Safety & Crevasse Rescue:</strong> Understand the risks of glacier travel and learn essential crevasse rescue techniques.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Mountaineering Equipment:</strong> Get hands-on experience with all the gear you need, from boots and harnesses to helmets and climbing protection.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Trip Planning & Navigation:</strong> Learn how to plan a successful mountaineering trip, including route finding, weather assessment, and emergency procedures.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Why Choose Our Course?</h2>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Certified Instructors:</strong> Our instructors are certified by leading mountaineering organizations and have years of experience leading expeditions.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Small Class Size:</strong> With a maximum of 10 participants, you\'ll receive personalized attention and plenty of time for one-on-one instruction.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Stunning Location:</strong> The course is held in a beautiful alpine environment, providing the perfect backdrop for learning and adventure.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Hands-On Learning:</strong> We believe in learning by doing. The majority of your time will be spent on the mountain, practicing the skills you learn.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Ready for the Challenge?</h2>\r\n        <p>This course is physically demanding, but no prior experience is required. A basic level of fitness and a sense of adventure are all you need. All necessary technical equipment will be provided. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-08-10</strong>. Spaces are limited, so secure your spot and start your mountaineering journey today!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 10, '350.00', '2', '2025-08-10 00:00:00', '2025-08-15', '2025-08-16', 'Upcoming', 'Beginner', 1, 99, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(3, 'Advanced Rock Climbing Course', 2, 'Lead climbing, belaying, anchor systems on multi-pitch routes.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Advanced Rock Climbing Course Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Advanced Rock Climbing Course: Taking Your Skills to the Next Level</h1>\r\n    <p>Ready to move beyond top-roping? Our \"Advanced Rock Climbing Course\" is a comprehensive 3-day program designed for experienced climbers who want to master multi-pitch routes and lead climbing. This course focuses on advanced techniques, safety systems, and the mental fortitude required for bigger climbs.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Course Curriculum: The Path to Mastery</h2>\r\n        <p>Led by expert guides, this course will push your limits and deepen your understanding of climbing safety and efficiency. We\'ll tackle complex scenarios and teach you the skills needed to confidently lead and belay on multi-pitch climbs.</p>\r\n        <p>Key topics include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Lead Climbing:</strong> Learn proper lead belaying, clipping techniques, and risk management.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Anchor Systems:</strong> Master building secure and redundant anchors for top-roping and multi-pitch transitions.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Multi-Pitch Climbing:</strong> Develop efficient climbing and belaying practices for multi-pitch routes, including communication and rope management.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Advanced Rescue Techniques:</strong> Get a solid foundation in essential self-rescue and partner-rescue techniques.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Route Planning:</strong> Learn how to read guidebooks, assess routes, and plan for a successful multi-pitch ascent.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Is This Course for You?</h2>\r\n        <p>This course is for experienced climbers who are comfortable with outdoor climbing and have a solid foundation in basic climbing techniques. You should be able to comfortably climb at least 5.8 on a top-rope. Our small class size ensures a focused and personalized learning environment.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Gear Up for a Challenge</h2>\r\n        <p>All technical climbing equipment will be provided, but participants are encouraged to bring their own gear to get comfortable with it. The course will be held on challenging multi-pitch routes, providing a real-world learning experience. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-07-25</strong>, so don\'t miss this opportunity to become a more confident and skilled climber!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 8, '500.00', '3', '2025-07-25 00:00:00', '2025-08-01', '2025-08-03', 'Completed', 'Advanced', 0, 63, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(4, 'Annapurna Circuit Trek', 3, 'A stunning 14-day trek through Nepal\'s Annapurna range.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Annapurna Circuit Trek Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Annapurna Circuit Trek: A 14-Day Himalayan Odyssey</h1>\r\n    <p>Venture into the heart of the Annapurna massif on our 14-day Annapurna Circuit Trek. This is one of the world\'s most famous treks, offering an incredible diversity of landscapes, from lush rice paddies and subtropical forests to alpine meadows and a high-altitude desert. The journey takes you through traditional villages, offering a glimpse into the rich cultural heritage of Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Journey: A Circular Route of Wonders</h2>\r\n        <p>Our trek follows a classic circular route, crossing the Thorong La Pass, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. The itinerary is designed to allow for gradual acclimatization, ensuring a safe and memorable experience. We\'ll start in the lower valleys and slowly make our way up, enjoying the changing scenery and diverse cultures.</p>\r\n        <p>Highlights of the trek include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Diverse Landscapes:</strong> Trek through a dramatic range of ecosystems, from subtropical lowlands to arid, moon-like landscapes.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Thorong La Pass:</strong> Conquer the 5,416m pass, a monumental achievement and the highest point of the trek.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Cultural Immersion:</strong> Experience the unique cultures of the Gurung, Manangi, and Thakali people.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Stunning Views:</strong> Enjoy panoramic views of some of the world\'s highest peaks, including Annapurna I, Dhaulagiri, and Machhapuchhre.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Muktinath Temple:</strong> Visit the sacred temple of Muktinath, a pilgrimage site for both Hindus and Buddhists.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Preparation & Fitness</h2>\r\n        <p>This is a moderate to challenging trek, suitable for trekkers with a good level of fitness and stamina. While no technical climbing is involved, the long days of walking and high altitude can be demanding. We recommend training with regular cardio and strength exercises before the trek. Our experienced guides will be with you every step of the way, providing support and sharing their knowledge of the region.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Book Your Adventure</h2>\r\n        <p>Our Annapurna Circuit Trek is an all-inclusive package, covering accommodation in local teahouses, all meals, and necessary permits. We handle all the logistics so you can focus on the stunning scenery and the challenge ahead. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-09-10</strong>. Don\'t miss your chance to experience this legendary Himalayan trek!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 16, '980.00', '14', '2025-09-10 00:00:00', '2025-09-25', '2025-10-08', 'Completed', 'Moderate', 1, 9, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 17:44:15'),
(5, 'Snow Climbing Skills', 1, 'Learn how to traverse snowfields and ascend icy slopes safely.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Snow Climbing Skills Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Snow Climbing Skills: Master the Fundamentals of Snow Travel</h1>\r\n    <p>Our \"Snow Climbing Skills\" course is a focused, 1-day workshop designed to teach you how to safely and efficiently traverse snowfields and ascend icy slopes. This course is perfect for hikers, trekkers, and aspiring mountaineers who want to gain confidence and competence in snowy conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Course Curriculum: Practical, Hands-on Learning</h2>\r\n        <p>This intensive workshop is all about practical application. You\'ll spend the day on the snow, learning and practicing essential techniques under the guidance of our certified instructors. The goal is to give you the skills you need to be self-sufficient and safe in a winter environment.</p>\r\n        <p>Key topics include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Ice Axe Use:</strong> Learn the correct way to hold, carry, and use an ice axe for balance and self-arrest.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Crampon Skills:</strong> Master various crampon walking techniques, including French, German, and American stepping.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Self-Arrest:</strong> This is a crucial skill. You will practice arresting a fall on a snow slope using your ice axe, a skill that could save your life.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Route Finding:</strong> Learn how to assess a snow slope for potential hazards and choose a safe and efficient route.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Winter Gear:</strong> Get an overview of essential winter gear and clothing and how to use it properly.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Who is This Course For?</h2>\r\n        <p>This course is a beginner-friendly workshop, suitable for anyone with a basic level of fitness and a desire to learn. No prior snow travel experience is necessary. We will provide all the necessary technical equipment, including ice axes and crampons.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Perfect Introduction to Winter Adventures</h2>\r\n        <p>By the end of the day, you\'ll have the foundational skills and confidence to tackle more challenging winter routes. The course is a great stepping stone to our \"Intro to Mountaineering\" or \"Winter Mountaineering\" courses. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-07-30</strong>, so book your spot and prepare for your next winter adventure!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 10, '250.00', '1', '2025-07-30 00:00:00', '2025-08-30', '2025-08-30', 'Published', 'Beginner', 0, 95, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(6, 'Kilimanjaro Expedition', 3, 'Summit Africa\'s highest mountain via the Machame Route.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Kilimanjaro Expedition Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Kilimanjaro Expedition: Summit Africa\'s Highest Peak</h1>\r\n    <p>Join us on an unforgettable 7-day expedition to summit Mount Kilimanjaro, Africa\'s highest mountain. Our carefully planned trip takes you via the scenic and challenging Machame Route, known for its stunning views and high success rate. This is not just a climb; it is a journey through five distinct climatic zones, from lush rainforest to arctic summit.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Machame Route: A Path of Beauty and Challenge</h2>\r\n        <p>The Machame Route, often called the \"Whiskey Route,\" is a popular choice for good reason. It offers a great balance of beauty and challenge, with a \"climb high, sleep low\" profile that aids in acclimatization. Our experienced team of guides and porters will ensure your safety and comfort every step of the way.</p>\r\n        <p>Key highlights of the expedition include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Lush Rainforests:</strong> Begin your journey through the vibrant rainforests of the lower slopes.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Shira Plateau:</strong> Enjoy the breathtaking views from the Shira Plateau, a UNESCO World Heritage site.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Lava Tower:</strong> Trek to the iconic Lava Tower and witness the dramatic volcanic landscape.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Barafu Camp:</strong> Prepare for the final summit push from the high-altitude Barafu Camp.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Uhuru Peak:</strong> Stand at the summit of Africa, watching the sunrise over the clouds.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Preparation for the Climb</h2>\r\n        <p>Mount Kilimanjaro is a non-technical climb, but it is physically demanding. A high level of fitness and mental determination is essential. We will provide you with a comprehensive training plan and a detailed packing list to help you prepare. Our guides will also lead you through daily briefings and health checks to monitor your acclimatization.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Book Your African Adventure</h2>\r\n        <p>Our all-inclusive package covers all park fees, meals, accommodation in tents, and the services of our professional team. We handle the logistics so you can focus on the climb. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-10-01</strong>. This is your chance to stand on the roof of Africa!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 14, '1800.00', '7', '2025-10-01 00:00:00', '2025-10-10', '2025-10-16', 'Published', 'Hard', 0, 103, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(7, 'Fansipan Summit Challenge', 3, 'Climb Vietnam\'s roof: Fansipan, via the Tram Ton trail.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Fansipan Summit Challenge Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Fansipan Summit Challenge: Conquer the Roof of Indochina</h1>\r\n    <p>Join us for a thrilling 2-day expedition to the summit of Fansipan, the highest mountain in Vietnam and the entire Indochina region. Our journey takes you via the scenic Tram Ton trail, offering a challenging yet rewarding trekking experience with stunning views of the Hoang Lien Son mountain range. This is a perfect adventure for those seeking a short but intense mountain climb.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Tram Ton Route: The Path of Least Resistance</h2>\r\n        <p>The Tram Ton trail is considered the most accessible route to Fansipan\'s summit, but it is by no means easy. The trail winds through dense forests, across streams, and up steep inclines, testing your endurance and determination. Our experienced local guides will lead the way, sharing their knowledge of the local flora and fauna.</p>\r\n        <p>The 2-day itinerary includes:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 1: Trekking to Base Camp.</strong> We\'ll start at the Tram Ton Pass and trek through lush forest to our base camp, where we\'ll spend the night in a mountain hut.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Day 2: Summit Push & Descent.</strong> We\'ll wake up early for the final push to the summit, where we\'ll be rewarded with a spectacular sunrise view. After celebrating our achievement, we\'ll descend back to the Tram Ton Pass.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>What to Expect & How to Prepare</h2>\r\n        <p>This is a challenging trek that requires a good level of physical fitness. You should be prepared for steep ascents and descents and be comfortable with trekking for long hours. We recommend training with regular cardio exercises before the trip. Our all-inclusive package covers all meals, accommodation, permits, and the services of our experienced guides.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Book Your Vietnamese Adventure</h2>\r\n        <p>The Fansipan Summit Challenge is a fantastic opportunity to experience the natural beauty of Northern Vietnam and push your limits. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-08-20</strong>. Book your spot and get ready to stand on the roof of Indochina!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 10, '320.00', '2', '2025-08-20 00:00:00', '2025-08-30', '2025-08-31', 'Upcoming', 'moderate', 1, 33, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(8, 'Matterhorn Technical Climb', 1, 'Ascend the iconic Matterhorn with a certified alpine guide.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Matterhorn Technical Climb Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Matterhorn Technical Climb: Ascend the Iconic Peak</h1>\r\n    <p>The Matterhorn is a symbol of alpine climbing, and our 2-day technical climb offers you the chance to ascend this iconic peak with a certified alpine guide. This is a serious alpine climb that requires a high level of fitness, technical climbing skills, and mental fortitude. We will guide you on the classic Hörnli Ridge route, the most famous way to the summit.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Climb: A Test of Skill and Endurance</h2>\r\n        <p>This is not a trek, but a true alpine climb. The Hörnli Ridge involves sustained scrambling, exposed rock climbing, and some snow and ice travel. Our guides are highly experienced and certified to ensure your safety on this demanding route. The 2-day itinerary is designed to maximize your summit chances and provide a safe and rewarding experience.</p>\r\n        <p>Key aspects of the climb:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Guide-to-Client Ratio:</strong> For safety, we maintain a strict 1:1 guide-to-client ratio, ensuring you get the personalized attention and support you need.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Technical Climbing:</strong> You will use ropes, harnesses, and other climbing equipment throughout the ascent and descent.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Hörnli Hut:</strong> We\'ll spend the night at the historic Hörnli Hut, the base camp for the Matterhorn climb.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Early Morning Summit Push:</strong> The summit push begins in the pre-dawn hours to take advantage of favorable conditions.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Who is This for?</h2>\r\n        <p>This climb is for experienced alpinists and climbers only. You must have prior experience with multi-pitch rock climbing, glacier travel, and a very high level of fitness. We will conduct a thorough screening of all participants to ensure they are prepared for the rigors of the climb. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-08-01</strong>.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>The Ultimate Alpine Challenge</h2>\r\n        <p>To stand on the summit of the Matterhorn is a monumental achievement. This climb is a test of your physical and mental strength, but the rewards are immeasurable. We will provide all necessary technical equipment. Book your spot and get ready for the ultimate alpine challenge!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 6, '2100.00', '2', '2025-08-01 00:00:00', '2025-08-12', '2025-08-13', 'In Progress', 'Expert', 0, 60, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 04:28:59'),
(9, 'Climbing Basics Workshop', 2, 'Introductory climbing course for all skill levels.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Climbing Basics Workshop Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Climbing Basics Workshop: Your Introduction to the World of Climbing</h1>\r\n    <p>Our \"Climbing Basics Workshop\" is the perfect starting point for anyone interested in rock climbing. This 1-day course is designed for complete beginners and those with minimal experience, providing a fun and safe introduction to the sport. You\'ll learn the essential skills needed to climb with confidence, whether you plan to climb indoors or outdoors.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Course Curriculum: A Solid Foundation</h2>\r\n        <p>Our certified instructors will guide you through all the fundamentals, from tying knots to belaying. The workshop is hands-on, with plenty of time for practice and personalized feedback. We aim to make you feel comfortable and confident on the wall.</p>\r\n        <p>Key topics include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Basic Knots:</strong> Learn essential climbing knots, including the figure-eight follow-through.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Belaying:</strong> Master the use of a belay device to safely manage the rope for your climbing partner.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Climbing Techniques:</strong> Learn fundamental climbing movements, including footwork and body positioning.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Understand the standard climbing commands for clear and safe communication.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Climbing Safety:</strong> Get an overview of safety protocols and risk management in a climbing environment.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Who is This Workshop For?</h2>\r\n        <p>This workshop is for all skill levels, from those who have never climbed before to those who want a refresher on the basics. No prior experience is necessary. All climbing equipment, including harness, shoes, and belay device, will be provided. The workshop is held in a safe and controlled environment, perfect for beginners.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Start Your Climbing Journey</h2>\r\n        <p>The \"Climbing Basics Workshop\" is a great way to discover a new passion and connect with the climbing community. Our instructors are passionate about climbing and dedicated to helping you succeed. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-07-22</strong>. Book your spot and get ready to reach new heights!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 4, '150.00', '1', '2025-07-22 00:00:00', '2025-07-28', '2025-07-28', 'Published', 'Beginner', 0, 1, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-14 12:26:41'),
(10, 'Winter Mountaineering – Ben Nevis', 1, 'Navigate harsh snow terrain on the UK\'s highest peak.', '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Winter Mountaineering – Ben Nevis Details</title>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <h1>Winter Mountaineering – Ben Nevis: The Ultimate Winter Skills Course</h1>\r\n    <p>Our 2-day \"Winter Mountaineering – Ben Nevis\" course is designed to equip you with the skills and confidence to navigate the challenging winter terrain of the Scottish Highlands. Ben Nevis, the UK\'s highest mountain, provides the perfect training ground to learn essential winter mountaineering techniques under the guidance of our expert instructors. This course is for those with some hill-walking experience who want to progress to winter conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Course Curriculum: Conquer the Cold</h2>\r\n        <p>This course is an intensive, hands-on experience focused on practical skills. You\'ll spend two days on the mountain, learning to deal with snow, ice, and harsh weather conditions. Our small group sizes ensure you get plenty of individual attention and coaching.</p>\r\n        <p>Key topics include:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Ice Axe & Crampon Use:</strong> Master the fundamental techniques for safe and efficient travel on snow and ice.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Winter Navigation:</strong> Learn how to navigate in a winter environment using a map, compass, and GPS, even in low visibility.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Avalanche Awareness:</strong> Understand how to assess avalanche risk and make safe decisions in the mountains.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Emergency Procedures:</strong> Learn how to build snow shelters, use emergency equipment, and respond to common winter emergencies.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Route Planning:</strong> Get a solid foundation in planning winter mountain routes and assessing weather forecasts.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>Who is This Course For?</h2>\r\n        <p>This course is for hikers and trekkers with prior summer hill-walking experience. You should have a good level of fitness and be prepared for demanding days in cold, potentially wet and windy conditions. All technical equipment, including ice axes, crampons, and helmets, will be provided. A detailed gear list will be sent to all participants.</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n    <section>\r\n        <h2>A Gateway to Winter Adventures</h2>\r\n        <p>By the end of this course, you\'ll have the skills and knowledge to plan and execute your own winter hill walks and begin your journey into winter mountaineering. The registration deadline is <strong>2025-12-01</strong>. Don\'t miss your chance to master the mountains in winter!</p>\r\n    </section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n', 10, '600.00', '2', '2025-12-01 00:00:00', '2025-12-10', '2025-12-11', 'Published', 'Advanced', 0, 98, '2025-07-21 19:49:14', '2025-08-12 09:05:15');

