(46, 'Explorer 2.0', '<div class=\"woocommerce-product-details__short-description\" style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Liberation Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0.98px;margin-bottom:75px;orphans:2;text-align:left;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">\r\n    <p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px 0px 20px;\">\r\n        The Explorer 2.0\'s are ergonomic, slim and stylish and have been designed specifically for&nbsp;climbing in alpine environments.&nbsp;<br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        They feature a wide lens surface for maximum field of vision, removable side shields to block extreme sunlight at high elevations, strategically placed vents to increase airflow to prevent fogging, flexible, shock-absorbing inserts on the nose bridge to increase comfort and grip and&nbsp;360° adjustable temples for a highly customizable fit.&nbsp;<br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        Ideal for those requiring a regular fit (Sunglass Width: 130mm,&nbsp;Lens Height: 47mm,&nbsp;Bridge Distance: 11mm, Temple Length: 135mm,&nbsp;Lens Width: 61mm).\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">LENSES:</strong><br>\r\n        &nbsp;\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;list-style:disc;margin-bottom:20px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:20px;padding-left:30px;\">\r\n        <li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\r\n            <p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">\r\n                <a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(30, 135, 240);cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://julbo.us/pages/reactiv-photochromic-lens-technology\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">REACTIV</strong></a><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\"> </strong>lenses are photochromic and adjust to changing light conditions by getting lighter or darker depending on the amount of UV light present. These lenses are made of NXT (Trivex), which has the clarity of glass and exceptional durability and impact resistance.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\r\n            <p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">\r\n                <a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(30, 135, 240);cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.julbo.com/en_gb/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-our-spectron-lenses\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">SPECTRON</strong></a>&nbsp;lenses are made of polycarbonate, which is&nbsp;light and offers good impact resistance.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\r\n            <p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">\r\n                <a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(30, 135, 240);cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://julbo.us/blogs/news/polarized-lenses-always-essential#:~:text=The%20primary%20benefits%20of%20polarized%20lenses%20include%20superior,intensification%20of%20color%20and%20improved%20contrast%20and%20relief.\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">POLARIZED</strong></a><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\"> </strong>lenses provide superior protection against the